  , issueTitle = "Ensuring table and db exists"
  , issuePullRequest = Nothing
  , issueUrl =
      "https://api.github.com/repos/rethinkdb/rethinkdb/issues/3512"
  , issueCreatedAt = 2015 (-01) (-07) 09 : 29 : 44 UTC
  , issueBody =
      Just
        "In my practice, there are often need to be sure about existence needed dbs, tables and indexes.\r\n\r\nI think following syntax will be o'k:\r\n\r\n```javascript\r\nr.ensureDb('db_name')\r\n```\r\n\r\nAs equivalent to:\r\n\r\n```javascript\r\nr.dbList().contains('db_name').do(r.branch(r.row, r.db('db_name'), r.do(function(){\r\n  return r.dbCreate('db_name').do(function(){\r\n    return r.db('db_name');\r\n  });\r\n}));\r\n```\r\n\r\nAnd ensuring for table exists:\r\n\r\n```javascript\r\nvar tableOptions = {\r\n  primaryKey:'id',\r\n  durability:'hard'\r\n};\r\nr.db('db_name').ensureTable('table_name', tableOptions);\r\n```\r\n\r\nAs equivalent to:\r\n\r\n```javascript\r\nvar table = r.db('db_name').table('table_name');\r\nr.db('db_name').tableList().contains('table_name').do(r.brach(r.row, table, r.do(function(){\r\n  return r.db('db_name').tableCreate('table_name', tableOptions).do(function(){\r\n    return table;\r\n  });\r\n})));\r\n```\r\n\r\nAnd ensuring index existence:\r\n\r\n```javascript\r\nvar indexOptions = {};\r\nr.db('db_name').table('table_name').ensureIndex('index_name', indexFunction, indexOptions);\r\n```\r\n\r\nAs equivalent to:\r\n\r\n```javascript\r\nvar table = r.db('db_name').table('table_name');\r\ntable.indexList().contains('index_name').do(r.branch(r.row, table, r.do(function(){\r\n  return table.indexCreate('index_name', indexOptions).do(function(){\r\n    return table;\r\n  }));\r\n})));\r\n```\r\n\r\nI think following approach should be implemented at core level, not in drivers, to achieve fast performance in cases where inserts are often occurs in unexistent databases or tables."
